.TH "GAX" "1" "" "gax" "User Manual"
.SH NAME
gax \- Google Access CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]gax\f[R] \f[I]command\f[R] [\f[I]options\f[R]] [\f[I]args\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Sync Google Workspace (Sheets, Docs, Gmail, Calendar) to local files
that are human\-readable, machine\-readable, and git\-friendly.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Main
.SS clone
.TP
\f[B]gax clone\f[R] \f[I][URL]\f[R]
Clone a Google resource from URL.
\f[B]\-o, \[en]output\f[R]: Output file \f[B]\-f, \[en]format\f[R]:
Output format (for forms)
.SS checkout
.TP
\f[B]gax checkout\f[R] \f[I][URL]\f[R]
Checkout a Google resource from URL into a folder of individual files.
\f[B]\-o, \[en]output\f[R]: Output folder \f[B]\-f, \[en]format\f[R]:
Output format (for sheets)
.SS pull
.TP
\f[B]gax pull\f[R] \f[I]FILES\f[R]
Pull/update .gax.md file(s) or .gax.md.d folder(s) from their sources.
\f[B]\-v, \[en]verbose\f[R]: Verbose output
.SS push
.TP
\f[B]gax push\f[R] \f[I]FILES\f[R]
Push local .gax.md file(s) or .gax.md.d folder(s) to their sources.
\f[B]\-y, \[en]yes\f[R]: Skip confirmation prompts
\f[B]\[en]with\-formulas\f[R]: Interpret formulas (sheets only)
.SS Resources
.SS cal
